\backslash
subsection*{Objects:
 Singletons and Companions}
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

In Scala,
 we don't have 
\backslash
texttt{static} members.
 Instead,
 we have the 
\backslash
texttt{object} keyword,
 which defines a 
\backslash
textbf{Singleton}—
a class that has exactly one instance.
 When an object shares the same name as a class,
 it is called a 
\backslash
textbf{Companion Object}.
\end_layout

